nodes.title: ControlNet Models
widgets_values:
select an XL ControlNet model to match the pre-proprocessor
(1) Canny - diffusion_pytorch_model.fp16
(2) OpenPose - OpenPoseXL2
(3) Zoe depth - depth-zoe-xl-v1.0-controlnet
(4) LineArt - controlnet-sd-xl-1.0-softedge-dexined

*Model names may change

nodes.title: Multi-ControlNet Notes
widgets_values:
Place your image in ControlNet Image if you have ready made ControlNet images (e,.g. pose diagrams, or depth maps).

You can also load ControlNet images via the batch process.

Important: All image slots on the multi-ControlNet stacks must be connected. If any are disconnected you will get an error.

nodes.title: Batch Process Notes
widgets_values:
Configure a default batch path on first use.

Set to single_image when not in use.

Select mode = incremental and Batch Process Switch input = batch image on either ControlNet or Img2Img, but not on both.

Set the Batch Count in the Comfy UI menu to the number of images you want to process. Tick on Extra Options.

For Img2Img batches you also need to set the 4-way image switch to 1 and the Img2Img process Switch to img2img.

nodes.title: Setup and Tips
widgets_values:
On first use:
- select models and VAE
- select a default LoRA in each Load LoRA node
- select an upscale model
- select XL ControlNet models in Multi_ControlNet stack
- add a default image in each of the Load Images nodes (purple nodes)
- add a default image batch in the Load Image Batch nodes
- select the batch_size in CR Aspect Ratio SDXL
- set the filename_prefix in Save Image to your preferred sub-folder
- save a copy to use as a template

Tips:
- Notes can be opened by clicking on the dots (green nodes)
- Each optional component can be bypassed using logic switches (red nodes)
- The default setting for all logic switches is OFF (1)
- Use Comfyroll Manager to find any missing custom nodes
- Right-click on nodes and select Pin to pin/unpin the node
- Add a default image in img2img, even if you are not using it
